{"questionId":"22514107","questionHtml":"<p>Find the rate at which the height is changing when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>differentiating&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;implicitly&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mtext>d</mtext><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>(M1)(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Award <strong><em>M1</em></strong> for attempting to solve for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>, <strong><em>A1&nbsp;</em></strong>for a correct expression.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math> seen anywhere&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>289</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>289372</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for the correct value. Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for the correct units, independent of other marks.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[7 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22514107","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ1.7c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the rate at which the height is changing when h=10 cm.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadc